{"key":"processedPost-11761082","value":{"id":11761082,"first":11760457,"last":11761082,"when":1262574948,"utime":"01/04/10 05:15 AM","content":"If it's a brand new bag, there may not be many contaminant spores on the vermiculite, since it's manufactured at very high temperature.&nbsp; However, when the bag has been open for awhile, I've had non-treated verm develop cobweb mold many times, so I always spread it out on a cookie sheet and bake at 350F to 450F for at least half an hour.&nbsp; Longer if it's a thicker layer.<br />RR","title":"Re: should i bake my verm?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}